In a mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix or flour, sugar, ginger, soda and salt. Using hands, rub egg into mixture. In a saucepan, warm syrup and butter; stir into batter. Let stand for 3-4 minutes, then knead. Roll heaping teaspoonfuls into small balls. Place 2 in. apart on greased baking sheets. Bake at 325 degrees F for 12-15 minutes. Cookies will flatten and "crackle" when done.